1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the problem of finding the optimal input covariance that maximizes the worst-case secrecy rate subject to a sum power constraint. This is a classic problem in information theory, and hence cs.IT is the most likely sub-category. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with the problem of secure communication in the presence of an eavesdropper, which is a classic problem in cryptography and security. Hence, cs.CR is also a likely sub-category. 
3. cs.SI (Signal Processing) - The paper deals with the problem of finding the optimal input covariance, which is a signal processing problem. Hence, cs.SI is also a likely sub-category. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with a wiretap channel model, which is a classic problem in multimedia communication. Hence, cs.MM is also a possible sub-category. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the problem of secure communication, which is a classic problem in networking and internet architecture. Hence, cs.NI is also a possible sub-category.
